This is a Chinese name; the family name is Chen (Chéng in Mandarin).
John S. Chen (Chinese: 程守宗; pinyin: Chéng Shǒuzōng; Jyutping: cing4 sau2 zung1; born July 1, 1955) is a Hong Kong-born British-American businessman serving as executive chairman and chief executive officer of BlackBerry Ltd.[1] Previously, he served as the chief executive officer and president of Sybase, an independent software vendor specializing in data management, analytics, and mobility technology.[2] He is currently a director of Wells Fargo & Company and Walt Disney Company.



